Toke Makinwa | Doberre Media personality Toke Makinwa has opined that she does not believe the Nigerian government has accurate data of people infected with the novel coronavirus in the country. Taking to her Twitter page yesterday, the “On Becoming” author encouraged her followers to remain safe as they go about their activities. She tweeted: “So are we going to continue to believe there are no more cases of Corona Virus in Nigeria??? I don’t think they have accurate data, guys pls be safe out there.” Her tweet came on the heels of the March 17 confirmation by the Nigerian government of the third case of coronavirus in the country. Today March 18, the National Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) confirmed that five new cases of coronavirus has been confirmed in Nigeria. In a tweet made on its official page, the NCDC wrote: “@Fmohnigeria has announced 5 new cases of #COVID9 in NIgeria bringing the total number confirmed vases in Nigeria to 8. All 5 cases had a travel history to the UK/USA. We urge Nigerians to remain calm as public health response activities are intestifed across the country.” The World Health Organisation (WHO) has since declared coronavirus as a pandemic. 